are required for the\ndynamical solution of the cosmological constant problem. We consider the\npossible role of the local temperature $T_{\\rm loc}=2T_{\\rm H}$ in the decay of\nthe de Sitter space-time due to the energy exchange between the vacuum energy\nand relativistic matter with this temperature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 12 Jul 2020 13:37:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 29 Aug 2020 15:01:50 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 7 Sep 2020 13:12:44 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 26 Oct 2020 09:26:03 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 6 Dec 2020 11:11:30 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Mon, 19 Apr 2021 09:34:34 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Wed, 21 Apr 2021 12:16:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-22"}
